install arduine software and install library and packages of ESP8266 or ESP only ( both of them )
open code file ( .ino ) and select board ESP8266 ( NODE MCU 1.0 ESP-12E MODULE ) OR ( NODE MCU 0.9 ESP-12 MODULE) OR ( GENERIC ESP 8266 MODULE ) FROM TOOL OPTION
inset the auth code , hotspot username and password  in this option


char auth[] = "XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX";
char ssid[] = "hotspot-user-name";
char pass[] = "hotspot-password";

then goto sketch option and click on upload option 

after completed upload   it shows     upload done.

press rst button in node mcu device.

when device connected to online it glow blue light
connect to blynk app on your phone 

to get the supply on port 


enjoy :)
